																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Finding arm workouts no equipment necessary isn’t always easy. Unfortunately, most of us don’t have a full gym setup at home or the resources necessary to hit the gym.</p>



<p>This is why we decided to put together the following guide on arm workouts at home.&nbsp;</p>



<p>These exercises are easy to do and can be performed with only a few exercise bands and dumbbells. You can even use books or jugs of water in a pinch.</p>



<p>Not only that, but we’ve included the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/arms-and-shoulders-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">best exercises to build strong arms and shoulders</a>. Let’s get into it.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">10 At Home Arm Workouts</p>



<p>In this article, you’ll find more detailed information about the following ten exercises that can easily be done at home:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Triceps-Dips">Triceps Dips</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Lateral-Raises">Dumbbell Lateral Raises</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls">Dumbbell Bicep Curls</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Overhead-Tricep-Extension">Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Pullover">Dumbbell Pullover</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Band-Bicep-Curl">Band Bicep Curl</a></li>



<li><a href="#Resistance-Band-Pull-Apart">Resistance Band Pull Apart</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Band-Tricep-Kickbacks">Band Tricep Kickbacks</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Plank">Plank</a>.</li>



<li><a href="#Incline-Push-Ups">Incline Push-Ups</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">10 Best Arm Workouts At Home</h2>



<p>Ready to optimize the results of your home workouts? We’ve compiled a list of the top ten exercises that build strength with little to no equipment required.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Triceps-Dips">Triceps Dips</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/triceps-dips" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Triceps dips</a> are a simple bodyweight exercise usually performed on lateral bars at the gym. However, you can modify this exercise for home workouts by using benches, chairs, or even a couch and armchair.</p>



<p>This exercise is widely regarded as <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/331477905_A_COMPARATIVE_ELECTROMYOGRAPHICAL_INVESTIGATION_OF_TRICEPS_BRACHII_AND_PECTORALIS_MAJOR_DURING_FOUR_DIFFERENT_FREEHAND_EXERCISES" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">one of the best exercises</a> for strengthening the entire triceps muscle group. Additionally, it also targets the chest, shoulder, and upper back muscles, making it an effective all-around upper body strengthener.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Chair Chest Dip" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/981044032?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Triceps Dips Guide. Video: <span>Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How to do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by setting up something for you to do the dips on. This could be two chairs placed approximately two feet apart.</li>



<li>Step between the chairs and find a solid place to rest both hands. Depending on the height of the objects used, you may also start in a kneeling position.</li>



<li>Completely straighten your arms to lift yourself off the ground.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Then, lean forward at your torso while crossing your legs at the ankle with a slight bend at the knee.</li>



<li>Begin bending at your elbows and slowly lowering yourself down.</li>



<li>Continue until your elbows are bent at about 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Once you have reached the bottom of the movement, straighten your arms to return to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid locking your elbows at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>Engage your core to prevent your legs from swinging as you lift and lower the body.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–5</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3-4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Triceps Dips</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Lateral-Raises">Dumbbell Lateral Raises</h3>



<p>Lateral raises are considered by many experts to be one of the best <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/arm-workouts-for-women" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">arm workouts for women</a> to sculpt aesthetically pleasing shoulders. The same can be said for men who want shoulders that stand out.</p>



<p>This is because <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-lateral-raise" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell lateral raises</a> involve shoulder abduction, or moving the arm sideways away from the body. No other movement creates more activation through the lateral deltoid, which is <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7706677/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">activated up to 30.3%</a> during lateral raises.</p>



<p>If you don’t have dumbbells at home, you can also use bottles of water, heavy books, or other household objects instead.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Lateral Raises" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/981404489?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Lateral Raises Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart with a weight in each hand.</li>



<li>Engage your core and draw your shoulders down the back.</li>



<li>With a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms to the sides until they align with your shoulders.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid using momentum to lift the dumbbells. Instead, focus on maintaining slow and controlled movements.</li>



<li>To prevent unnecessary strain on the elbow joint, keep a slight bend into the elbows during the lift.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–5</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Dumbbell Lateral Raises</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls">Dumbbell Bicep Curls</h3>



<p>Due to their simple execution, <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-bicep-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell bicep curls</a> are an ideal addition to at home arm workouts without weights.</p>



<p>As the name suggests, the bicep curl mainly targets the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519538/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">biceps muscles</a>. These include the long and short heads, which are responsible for bending the elbow. <br>However, the deltoid and forearm muscles, which help stabilize the shoulder and grip heavy objects, also <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10054060/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">benefit from this exercise</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Bicep Curls" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/978260838?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Bicep Curls Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Find two dumbbells or objects that are a suitable weight for you to lift. Something that you can lift without sacrificing form.</li>



<li>Holding one in each hand, stand with your feet hip-width apart and knees slightly bent.</li>



<li>Engage your core and, as you breathe in, bend your elbows to draw the weights toward your shoulders.</li>



<li>As you breathe out, lower the weights to their starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Don’t allow the weights to simply drop as you’re lowering them. Focus on lowering them slowly while squeezing your bicep muscles.</li>



<li>If you cannot lift your weights without leaning backward, they are likely too heavy.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
