<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Overhead-Tricep-Extension">Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension</h3>



<p>Another effective exercise for working the triceps is the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-overhead-tricep-extension" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell overhead tricep extension</a>. </p>



<p>Compared to other tricep exercises, the arm positioning of overhead tricep extensions offers maximal <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35819335/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">long head hypertrophy potential</a>.</p>



<p>The triceps long head is an important muscle for <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulder stability</a> and plays an important role in heavy presses. This is because it is the only tricep muscle that connects to the shoulder blade.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Seated Triceps Extension" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/982969469?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Find a chair and either a dumbbell or something else to use as a weight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Sit down with a tall spine and grip your weight with both hands, palms facing upwards.</li>



<li>Starting with your elbows bent, take a deep breath in as you raise the dumbbell until it’s directly above your head.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stop when your arms are mostly extended but with a slight bend in your elbows.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbell by flexing your elbows to return to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>During the movement, focus on keeping your elbows tucked close to your ears. This is especially important during the lowering phase.</li>



<li>Maintain your neck position as you move. You shouldn’t have to tuck your chin to make space for the weight behind the head.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
