<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Pullover">Dumbbell Pullover</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-pullover" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell pullover</a> is a compound exercise that simultaneously strengthens several major muscle groups. These include the chest, latissimus dorsi, and core muscles; particularly the rectus abdominus. </p>



<p>These all play an important role in stabilizing and providing power during compound lifts. Particularly the rectus abdominis, which is <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/12/21/11138" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">the most active</a> during the dumbbell pullover.</p>



<p>This muscle helps stabilize the core, providing a solid foundation for lifting heavy weights.  Strong rectus abdominis muscles can allow for better control, thus reducing your risk of injury.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Pullover" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/984680529?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Pullover Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Find a bench or backless chair and an appropriate weight.</li>



<li>Lie with your back flat on the bench, your legs bent at a 90-degree angle. Your feet should be firmly planted around shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Hold your weight with both hands, palms facing up.</li>



<li>Extend your arms directly above your chest while maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc-like motion over your head.</li>



<li>Lower the weight until your arms are in line with your torso or you feel a stretch in your chest and lats.</li>



<li>Return to the starting position by straightening your arms to bring the dumbbell above your chest.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>As you lower the weight behind the head, increase the bend in your elbows. Doing so will enhance activation through the triceps.</li>



<li>Maintain control over the weight throughout the entire movement to help prevent muscle strains and other injuries.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



