<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Band-Bicep-Curl">Band Bicep Curl</h3>



<p>As you might expect, band bicep curls are a bicep-dominant exercise that strengthens both heads of the muscle group.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Studies show that practicing the banded bicep curl with your hands supinated (palms facing up), helps to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10054060/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improve bicep activation</a>. Other grips, such as a pronated grip (palms facing up), are better for targeting the anterior deltoids and (brachioradialis) forearm muscles.</p>



<p>A strong grip is required for proper performance of the band bicep curl. An easy way to enhance your forearm strength is by incorporating <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-forearm-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">forearm dumbbell exercises</a> in your workout regime.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Band Bicep Curl" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1002673876?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Band Bicep Curl Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand in the middle of your resistance band with your feet shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold the ends or handles on the band in each hand with a supinated grip (palms facing up).</li>



<li>Stand upright with your arms fully extended by your sides. Lift your chest, bring your shoulders back, and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hugging your elbows close to your sides, slowly bend your elbows and curl your hands toward your shoulders.</li>



<li>At the top of the movement, pause and focus on squeezing your biceps.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Gradually lower your hands back down to return to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Before beginning the movement, ensure the band is securely under your feet to keep it from hitting you.</li>



<li>Maintain steady tension on the band throughout the entire movement.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
