<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Resistance-Band-Pull-Apart">Resistance Band Pull Apart</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/resistance-band-pull-apart" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">resistance band pull apart</a> replicates the movement of flyes, a popular exercise for strengthening the shoulders and upper back.</p>



<p>Nonetheless, its ability to target the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8975561/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">posterior deltoid and trapezius muscles</a> makes it a valuable addition to any home arm workout.</p>



<p>The posterior deltoid and trapezius muscles, due to their positioning, can be difficult to target.&nbsp;</p>



<p>However, strengthening these muscles can improve the performance of both pushing and pulling exercises. These exercises include rows, pull-ups, push-ups, and even bench press.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Resistance Band Pull Apart" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/984663374?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Resistance Band Pull Apart Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Hold your resistance band with both hands using a pronated (palms facing down) grip. Your arms should be approximately shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent. Engage your core to support an upright posture throughout the exercise.</li>



<li>Hold the band in front of you with your arms straight and wrists neutral.</li>



<li>Slowly pull the band apart by moving your arms outward to the sides.</li>



<li>Maintaining control over the band as you move, bring your hands back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Select a resistance band with moderate tension. You should feel challenged during the exercise but not have to sacrifice proper form.</li>



<li>Keep your wrists neutral throughout the entire movement. Avoid allowing your wrists to be pulled back.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
