<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Band-Tricep-Kickbacks">Band Tricep Kickbacks</h3>



<p>Another ideal isolation exercise for targeting and strengthening the triceps is banded tricep kickbacks.&nbsp;</p>



<p>As the name suggests, during this bent-over exercise, you do a kicking back-type motion to straighten the arms. This quick extension of the elbows helps to activate the triceps.</p>



<p>Because the elbow is positioned close to the torso during this exercise, the triceps long head is the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6136322/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">driving force</a>. This is the only triceps muscle <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">connecting to the scapula</a> (shoulder blade) and is therefore very important to shoulder stabilization. </p>



<p>Strengthening the triceps long head muscles enhances power and stability during heavy lifts.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Band Tricep Kickback" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1002222804?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Band Tricep Kickbacks Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Place a resistance band under both feet with one end in each hand.</li>



<li>Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keeping your upper arms close to your torso, bring around a 90-degree bend to your elbows.</li>



<li>Draw your hands backward to straighten your arms until your arm is fully extended.</li>



<li>Focus on squeezing the tricep at the top of the movement before slowly returning your hands to their starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>When learning how to perform this exercise, you may choose to do one hand at a time so you can master your form.</li>



<li>Do not reposition your elbows during the movement. They should remain fixed with only your hand and forearms moving.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
