<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Plank">Plank</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/plank" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Planks</a> are a classic body-weight exercise that can be performed anywhere without the need for a single piece of equipment.</p>



<p>Like push-ups, this exercise has gained popularity due to its ability to simultaneously <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10766451/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">target several muscle groups</a> at once. These include the upper and lower abs, gluteus, back, oblique, and deltoid muscles.</p>



<p>Because of this multi-muscle involvement and ability to strengthen the core, planks have even been shown to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8399219/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduce back pain</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Plank" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980209730?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Plank Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Starting on your hands and knees, place your hands directly under your shoulders.</li>



<li>Step your legs back until you are on the balls of your feet. Straighten both your knees to keep your legs lifted off the ground.</li>



<li>Engage your core muscles to neutralize your spine.</li>



<li>Hold this position for the desired amount of time.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Continue drawing your heels away from you to maintain tension in the lower body.</li>



<li>If you have weak wrists or inadequate strength, you can rest on your forearms instead of your hands.</li>
</ul>



