<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Incline-Push-Ups">Incline Push-Ups</h3>



<p>Kneeling and <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/incline-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">incline push-ups</a> are two popular push-up variations that are ideal for <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/beginner-arm-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">beginner arm workouts</a>. They’re also a perfect option for your at-home workout since they’re one of the few arm workouts without weights. </p>



<p>All you need to perform this push-up variation is a stable elevated surface for you to place your hands onto. The higher the angle, the easier it will be for you to perform this exercise. So keep that in mind when choosing your surface.</p>



<p>Push-ups <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5812863/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">target several muscles simultaneously</a>, which is why they’re such a popular exercise option. With a single exercise, you can strengthen the chest, core, shoulder, back, tricep, and forearm muscles.</p>



