<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Find a stable elevated surface that you can use. A chair, bench, or even your couch will work.</li>



<li>Assume a plank position, with your hands placed shoulder-width apart on the surface. Your arms and legs should be completely straight.</li>



<li>With a neutral back position, your chest up, and head facing forward begin bending your elbows.</li>



<li>When you reach the bottom of the movement, pause briefly, maintaining a tight body position.</li>



<li>Straighten your arms to push back up to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows tucked closely into your body during the movement.</li>



<li>Place your hands right under your shoulders during the setup.</li>
</ul>



