<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Biceps</h3>



<p>One of the more well-known upper body muscles, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519538/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">the biceps</a> are located on the front of the upper arm. They have two heads, a long head, and a short head. Both of these originate at the scapula (shoulder blade) and attach to the radius (forearm bone).</p>



<p>The main role of the biceps muscles is flexing, or bending, the elbow. Of the exercises in this article, dumbbell and banded bicep curls are the best for bicep strengthening.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Triceps</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">The triceps</a> is a three-headed muscle that sits directly opposite the biceps on the back of the upper arm. </p>



<p>Both the lateral and medial heads start at the top of the humerus (upper arm bone) and insert into the ulna (forearm bone). For this reason, they are mainly involved in the extension, or straightening, of the arm.</p>



<p>The long head, however, originates from the scapula (shoulder blade). Because of this, it also plays a role in shoulder stabilization.</p>



<p>Anyone wanting to strengthen the triceps muscles should regularly perform tricep dips, dumbbell overhead tricep extensions, and tricep kickbacks.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Wrist Flexors</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK545198/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">wrist flexors</a> are a group of muscles located on the front side of the forearm. Their main function is to flex the wrist and fingers forward, toward the palm.</p>



<p>Because the wrist flexors are activated by gripping objects, they are best strengthened with dumbbells and banded bicep curls.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Wrist Extensors</h3>



<p>Directly opposite the wrist flexors, you’ll find the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534805/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">wrist extensors</a>. This is a collection of muscles responsible for extending, or straightening, the wrist and fingers.</p>



<p>Although these muscles can be tricky to target, you can work them using the resistance band pull-apart and planks.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Benefits Of At Home Arm Workouts</h2>



<p>Studies have shown home workouts to be effective in <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/366893292_Comparison_of_the_Effectiveness_of_Home-Based_Workouts_and_Gym_Training_according_to_Caloric_Intake#:~:text=Results%20showed%20that%20people%20who,heart%20rate%2C%20and%20Respiratory%20Rate" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reducing fat percentage and waist size</a>. </p>



<p>They can be used when you are short on time or can’t afford a gym membership for the following benefits:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Improves Appearance</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1.jpg" alt="arm workouts at home" class="wp-image-21872" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/arm-at-home-workouts-1-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">By not having to waste time traveling to and from a fitness center, it’s easier to create and maintain a consistent workout schedule. <span>Photo: Freepik</span></figcaption></figure>



<p>One benefit of a home workout routine is not having to waste time traveling to and from a fitness center. You also don’t have to have to switch up your workouts as the temperature changes between seasons.</p>



<p>For that reason, it’s easier to create and maintain a consistent workout schedule. Which is regarded by many as the most important factor in creating lasting changes to your physique.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Supports Posture</h3>



<p>Poor posture affects as much as 80% of Americans and can lead to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7579401/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">chronic back and shoulder pain</a>. Luckily, it can be prevented or reversed by strengthening the body. Particularly the various upper body muscle groups, many of which are targeted in the ten exercises outlined in this article.</p>



<p>For example, the plank strengthens not only the arm muscles, but also the shoulder, back, and core muscles. All of which contribute to an upright and comfortable posture.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Balances Physique</h3>



<p>Regularly performing arm workouts can help you enhance the strength and muscle size of your upper body muscles. Thus, ensuring that your arm, shoulder, and upper back muscles are developed proportionally to the rest of your body.</p>



<p>This balance is essential to preventing the common issue of muscular imbalances. Having a well-developed lower body or core with comparatively weaker upper body muscles. This can affect athletic performance and general aesthetics.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Other Tips For Arm Workouts At Home </h2>



<p>When creating your at-home arm workout, ensure that you use a well-rounded combination of exercises. This means choosing exercises that target different muscle groups.</p>



<p>Ensuring that you target each muscle group will help you build a well-balanced physique that is free of muscular imbalances.</p>



<p>Keep in mind that it’s often the exercises that you feel tempted to skip that you should do the most often. As they are the ones that challenge the muscle groups that you lack strength in.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>



<p>You don’t need to have fancy equipment or a membership to a gym to begin building arm strength. Even a few resistance bands and kettlebells (or jugs of water if you’re in a pinch), will do the trick.</p>



<p>This article has outlined an arsenal of at-home arm workouts for you to choose from. Incorporate different exercises in each workout that target new muscle groups for optimal results. You’ll be well on your way to reaching all of your unique fitness goals.</p>



